We’ve all heard the terms Gen Z, Millennials, Gen X and Baby Boomers. But what do you really know about these groups? A lot of what we think we know is based on opinions, assumptions or stereotypes, instead of real data. Viacom has studied these demographics – and here’s some of the insights. Socio-cultural: Civil Rights Movement, cultural revolutions, Woodstock, Vietnam War Socio-cultural: AIDS epidemic, MTV and rise of cable news/pop culture Driven by ‘success’ Driven by ‘freedom’ FACT: Boomers lead very active lives and are tech savvy FACT: While often forgotten, Gen X actually started a lot of the innovation and disruption that’s often attributed to millennials Sociocultural: 9/11 and War on Terror Sociocultural: Climate Change, #MeToo, Black Lives Matter, Gun Violence, Refugee Crisis Driven by ‘meaning’ Driven by ‘creation’ FACT: Millennials are prospering in the face of financial adversity and want to see positive results from their actions FACT: They are still in their formative years and we’re still learning all about them Most were 10 or younger when the iPhone launched   Giuliana Dias is director: research & insights at Viacom International Media Networks (VIMN).  She is an experienced insights director with a demonstrated history of working in the broadcast media industry. Want to continue this conversation on The Media Online platforms? Comment on Twitter @MediaTMO or on our Facebook page. Send us your suggestions, comments, contributions or tip-offs via e-mail to glenda@wagthedog.co.za or michael@wagthedog.co.za